.
.Nx \*V
is the third major release for the \*M.
.Pp
Some notable \*M-specific improvements include:
.(bullet
Long standing bug in colormap handling code that resulted in very dim
console colors is fixed.
.It
.Xr j6x0lcd 4
and
.Xr j6x0tp 4
now support HP 620LX machines.
.It
.Xr j6x0pwr 4
supports very minimal power saving mode when On/Off button is pressed.
.bullet)
.Pp
.Nx \*V
on \*M is, as usual, also fully backward compatible with old
.Nx*M
binaries, so you don't need to recompile all your local programs
provided you set the appropriate binary compatibility options in your
kernel configuration.
